Finally, Theoretical Benefit and Limitation of Diffusion Language Models (Feng et al., 2025) analyzes fundamental
challenges of DLLMs, explicitly noting the difficulty of variable-length generation. Our work is complementary in that
it directly targets this limitation by introducing an inference-time framework for adaptive length determination, without
modifying the underlying model or training procedure. J. Case Study

J.1. Infilling

Python Infilling Example

def string_transformation(A: str, B: str, rules: list) -> Union[int, str]:

queue = deque([(A, 0)])
# Each element in the queue is a tuple (current_string, steps_taken)
visited = set([A])
# Keep track of visited strings to avoid loops

# Perform BFS
while queue:

current, steps = queue.popleft()
if current == B:

return steps
#BEGIN INFILLING
for source, target in rules:

new_current = current.replace(source, target)
if new_current not in visited:

visited.add(new_current)
queue.append((new_current, steps + 1))
#END INFILLING
return "NO ANSWER!"

